<div id="review_1326978745" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1326978745" />
    <a title="Angela M" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4685500-angela-m"><img alt="Angela M" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1640644927p2/4685500.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1326978745?book_show_action=true">Oct 04, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Angela M" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Angela M" href="/user/show/4685500-angela-m">Angela M</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4685500-angela-m?shelf=2021-favorites">2021-favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1326978745" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14972322641954398436"><br/>“Santino, the peasants—the contadini—will they help strangers?”<br/>“Si, certo, signore.”<br/>“Even Jews?”<br/>“We’re all human beings, signore. Even Turks and Africans.”<br/><br/>For those who love historical fiction, especially about WWII, you will be taken in. By its very nature as a war story, as a story of the Holocaust, it’s brutal and sad beyond words. I cried many times. But as the title implies, there are many threads of grace among the many characters and I was heartened. <br/><br/>While this is fiction, the novel is im</span>
  <span id="freeText14972322641954398436" style="display:none"><br />“Santino, the peasants—the contadini—will they help strangers?”<br />“Si, certo, signore.”<br />“Even Jews?”<br />“We’re all human beings, signore. Even Turks and Africans.”<br /><br />For those who love historical fiction, especially about WWII, you will be taken in. By its very nature as a war story, as a story of the Holocaust, it’s brutal and sad beyond words. I cried many times. But as the title implies, there are many threads of grace among the many characters and I was heartened. <br /><br />While this is fiction, the novel is impeccably researched and reflects the goodness and courage of the Italian people who saved thousands of Jews . It should go without saying, but we have to remember.<br /></span>
